TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=4
TASK_ID=48
TASK_TITLE=DRY refactor of TUI — extract shared patterns into reusable components
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W2
TASK_DESCRIPTION=CATEGORY: deep
MODEL: opus

User observes the TUI has standardized behavior patterns that are duplicated across views/components. Wants a DRY refactor so common concepts are reused, making the TUI more concise, easier to maintain, and ensuring a fix in one place applies everywhere.

PHASE 1 — RESEARCH (must complete before any code changes):
1. Audit tui/ for duplicated patterns: rendering logic, input handling, state management, styling, layout, list/table patterns, status display, key bindings
2. Map which files share similar structures — quantify the duplication
3. Identify candidate abstractions: shared components, common renderers, base models, style constants, layout helpers
4. Propose a refactor plan with specific extractions, ordered by impact

PHASE 2 — IMPLEMENTATION (after research review):
- Extract shared components/helpers
- Refactor views to use shared abstractions
- Ensure all existing behavior is preserved (no regressions)

Success criteria:
- Measurable reduction in duplicated code
- Common patterns extracted into reusable packages/functions
- A bug fix in a shared component automatically applies to all consumers
- No behavioral regressions
